WEBVTT

00:59.059 --> 01:00.393
-[Emily] Night.
-[woman] Night.

01:00.686 --> 01:01.853
-[man] Night, Em.
-[Emily] Night.

01:02.271 --> 01:03.938
-[man] See you tomorrow.
-[Emily] Good night.

01:08.777 --> 01:10.194
-Emily?
-Good night, Steven.

01:10.654 --> 01:13.072
-Aren't you leaving early?
-If anything, it's late.

01:15.242 --> 01:17.535
Incidentally, Emily, I think
the windmill is taking

01:17.536 --> 01:18.995
too much time
for the tour, so...

01:18.996 --> 01:20.496
Steven, the windmill is fine.

01:20.497 --> 01:21.706
No, no, I like the windmill--

01:21.707 --> 01:22.915
Can we talk about it tomorrow?

01:23.417 --> 01:27.545
Emily, this is important.
Why are you avoiding me?

01:27.921 --> 01:30.590
David, how can I avoid you?
We work in the same place.

01:31.467 --> 01:35.386
Now listen, Emily,
I'm having difficulty with--

01:35.387 --> 01:37.472
[exhales]
Steven, we're getting a divorce.

01:39.933 --> 01:41.059
[woman] Good night, Emily.

01:41.351 --> 01:42.310
[cash drawer opens]

01:48.734 --> 01:51.277
[weather news on radio]

02:11.090 --> 02:12.882
[music playing]

02:42.454 --> 02:43.454
[car door opening]

02:46.166 --> 02:47.125
Good night.

02:51.547 --> 02:52.547
[knocking on door]

03:00.931 --> 03:01.889
[door opening]

03:02.391 --> 03:03.558
You almost missed me.

03:03.559 --> 03:05.184
Almost. Thanks, Ira.

03:05.185 --> 03:06.144
See you tomorrow.

03:15.112 --> 03:17.446
[Emily humming a tune]

03:28.458 --> 03:29.417
[dog barking]

04:15.005 --> 04:16.088
[cat meowing]

04:16.089 --> 04:17.048
Shit.

04:21.553 --> 04:22.511
Hi, Jenny.

04:22.679 --> 04:23.846
[Emily screams]

04:26.391 --> 04:27.350
[cat screaming]

04:28.101 --> 04:29.060
[glass breaking]

04:29.728 --> 04:30.728
[Emily struggling]

04:32.272 --> 04:33.231
[Emily screams]

04:34.149 --> 04:35.149
[knife opening]

04:37.027 --> 04:38.069
[man breathing heavily]

04:47.120 --> 04:51.290
You yell,
the knife goes down your throat.

04:52.376 --> 04:53.542
You understand?

04:55.629 --> 04:59.715
Now I wanna hear you say,
"Yeah, I understand."

05:02.678 --> 05:04.929
Speak up. I can't hear you.

05:05.889 --> 05:08.891
Yes, I... I understand.

05:09.059 --> 05:10.768
[breathing nervously]

05:11.728 --> 05:12.895
You got underwear on?

05:14.147 --> 05:15.314
Don't hurt me please.

05:20.529 --> 05:23.531
What you got on?
Top and bottom, or what?

05:24.533 --> 05:25.491
Please.

05:26.368 --> 05:30.079
Show me, show me,
come on, lift your sweater.

05:31.748 --> 05:32.707
I can't.

05:33.208 --> 05:36.127
That's bullshit. You're crazy.

05:36.837 --> 05:40.840
Sure, you can. You better do it.

05:54.646 --> 05:56.063
[Emily crying]

06:01.153 --> 06:03.821
Now, pull it down, sweetheart.

06:10.162 --> 06:14.373
Hey, pull it down.

06:17.252 --> 06:18.961
No, no.

06:24.968 --> 06:25.926
Hey!

06:34.936 --> 06:36.687
Oh yeah.

06:37.939 --> 06:40.441
Pure tit.

06:44.905 --> 06:46.280
Now open your mouth.

06:49.409 --> 06:56.040
Say, "Ah."

06:57.167 --> 06:58.376
-Ah.
-[man grunting]

07:03.173 --> 07:05.466
-Ah.
-Ah.

07:07.677 --> 07:09.136
[grunting]

07:12.057 --> 07:15.101
You move. I cut.

07:20.440 --> 07:21.399
Please.

07:22.859 --> 07:24.360
Shut up and move it.

07:24.945 --> 07:28.197
Gonna make it sound
like you're having a ball.

07:28.865 --> 07:30.699
Now say, "Ah."

07:33.203 --> 07:37.790
Ah.

07:49.428 --> 07:51.762
[birds chirping]

08:09.281 --> 08:10.906
[chatter on police radio]

08:35.849 --> 08:39.351
[police radio] Frank investigate
a 10-10, 20 Plaza Street,

08:39.352 --> 08:41.102
Lincoln place
on Vanderbilt Avenue,

08:41.104 --> 08:41.979
it's in the street.

08:53.325 --> 08:55.451
[chatter on police radio]

09:01.625 --> 09:03.042
[dog barking]

09:04.669 --> 09:05.961
[birds chirping]

09:22.312 --> 09:23.604
[engine starting]

09:24.648 --> 09:25.606
[car door closing]

09:53.593 --> 09:56.303
If there’s something you can
remember about the incident?

09:59.349 --> 10:03.227
Or... any sort of description.

10:06.314 --> 10:07.273
Anything?

10:20.662 --> 10:22.204
We know how difficult this is.

10:25.000 --> 10:28.294
And you don't have to say
anything you don't wanna say.

10:28.712 --> 10:29.670
[knock on door]

10:30.422 --> 10:32.881
Emily? It's Andrea.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.305
[footsteps]

10:45.103 --> 10:46.645
Who are you?
I'm looking for Emily.

10:48.607 --> 10:49.690
A police officer.

10:54.404 --> 10:56.363
What's happening? Emily?

10:57.616 --> 10:58.574
[door closing]

11:00.952 --> 11:02.745
[Bob]
You're a friend? Miss...

11:02.954 --> 11:03.787
[Andrea] Glassen.

11:04.080 --> 11:05.914
-[Bob] Glassen.
-What's happening here?

11:07.667 --> 11:08.751
Someone broke in.

11:10.837 --> 11:11.879
She was assaulted.

11:14.215 --> 11:15.758
[policewoman]
Sit down, Miss Glassen.

11:16.718 --> 11:19.136
Sometimes a friend can help
make these things easier.

11:22.724 --> 11:23.932
[policewoman] Emily?

11:24.225 --> 11:26.185
If he's done
this kind of thing before,

11:26.770 --> 11:29.021
-and he's been--
-Just give her a chance.

11:30.023 --> 11:31.607
She used to have
some difficulty with--

11:31.608 --> 11:34.193
[Emily]
I can... speak for myself.

11:36.029 --> 11:39.573
I told you... it was dark.

11:41.242 --> 11:44.828
I... couldn't see.

11:49.167 --> 11:54.588
He wanted to hurt me.
He was very cruel.

11:58.009 --> 11:59.218
Miss Hollander,

12:01.930 --> 12:03.514
I know that you're at
a disadvantage.

12:07.310 --> 12:08.394
And I realize,

12:08.395 --> 12:10.479
it's not gonna be easy for you
to give us a description.

12:12.857 --> 12:14.191
To describe what he did.

12:14.859 --> 12:16.318
[Andrea] You're making her
nervous.

12:20.615 --> 12:22.116
Would you like to try
and write it down?

12:22.992 --> 12:24.201
Might be easier.

12:30.333 --> 12:32.167
He's gonna be real hard
to catch, you know.

12:34.963 --> 12:36.046
Unless you help me.

12:38.508 --> 12:39.591
You understand?

12:40.093 --> 12:43.011
You are.
You're making her nervous.

12:49.185 --> 12:50.144
Look...

12:52.272 --> 12:54.440
I just don't want this
to happen to anyone else.

12:58.737 --> 13:00.320
So what I really need here is...

13:02.031 --> 13:03.615
you know,
just some small detail.

13:06.578 --> 13:08.078
A piece of his clothing...

13:09.581 --> 13:11.665
if you can remember his voice...

13:14.085 --> 13:17.963
or his face.
Whenever you can.

13:26.139 --> 13:29.183
You can call that number there,
or you can just stop by.

13:30.351 --> 13:32.478
And I'll be there
to listen to you.

13:35.857 --> 13:36.690
Okay?

13:49.162 --> 13:51.288
[floor creaking]

14:00.256 --> 14:01.590
[door closing]

14:13.102 --> 14:14.478
[dog barking]

14:16.105 --> 14:17.898
You don't have to tell him
anything, you know.

14:20.985 --> 14:22.486
He's never gonna catch
who did it.

14:31.663 --> 14:32.955
I'll make some coffee.

14:33.915 --> 14:34.873
We'll talk.

14:47.595 --> 14:49.054
[water running]

14:57.146 --> 15:01.316
I've been thinking,
after what's happened,

15:01.317 --> 15:03.026
you shouldn't stay here alone,
you know.

15:03.945 --> 15:06.280
-[Emily] A... Andrea?
-Yes?

15:07.657 --> 15:10.033
I'm... sorry.

15:11.578 --> 15:15.956
Would you... please leave now?

15:23.965 --> 15:25.215
Sure, if you like.

15:26.050 --> 15:29.553
I... wanna work this,
this out, by myself.

15:49.198 --> 15:50.157
[door closing]

15:52.160 --> 15:53.619
[Emily sighs]

15:56.456 --> 15:57.414
[cat meows]

16:00.919 --> 16:02.753
[Emily cries]
Oh, Jenny.

16:09.385 --> 16:11.428
[phone ringing]

16:12.096 --> 16:13.722
[man] Alright,
if you just sign at the X.

16:15.058 --> 16:18.143
I suppose you realize how lucky
you are to catch one available.

16:18.645 --> 16:21.688
[Emily] Yes. Thank you.

16:25.818 --> 16:27.152
Now we need the check, huh.

16:27.820 --> 16:29.613
Oh, I'm sorry.

16:35.620 --> 16:36.662
[Emily clears throat]

16:36.871 --> 16:38.372
[phone ringing]

16:52.303 --> 16:54.554
And remember, no pets.

18:02.957 --> 18:06.168
-[ship horn]
-[whistle blowing]

18:34.781 --> 18:35.739
[door bell ringing]

18:37.825 --> 18:38.784
[woman] Who is it?

18:39.202 --> 18:42.245
[Emily] Hi, it's your
new neighbor from 6-G.

18:42.580 --> 18:43.538
[woman] Yes?

18:44.791 --> 18:50.170
My phone isn't in yet,
and I was wondering if I--

18:51.547 --> 18:53.799
-Come in.
-[Emily] Thank you.

18:57.345 --> 18:58.553
It's over there.

19:13.486 --> 19:14.778
[phone ringing]

19:16.364 --> 19:17.864
-Hello.
-[Emily] Steven?

19:18.658 --> 19:21.493
Emily. I was just working late.

19:21.494 --> 19:23.203
We are adding a piece
of equipment here.

19:23.496 --> 19:24.496
[Emily] Uh...

19:24.497 --> 19:25.789
Hey, what happened
to you by the way?

19:25.957 --> 19:27.124
You weren't at work today.

19:27.583 --> 19:28.834
I called, but...

19:29.418 --> 19:32.379
Steven,
I can't talk right now. I...

19:33.506 --> 19:34.422
I...

19:35.466 --> 19:37.259
Something came up
and I need your help.

19:37.969 --> 19:38.927
[Steven] Really?

19:39.887 --> 19:42.222
I have to move right away,
tomorrow morning.

19:43.516 --> 19:44.474
What about work?

19:46.018 --> 19:48.562
Steven, I need your help.

19:49.188 --> 19:50.021
I don’t know.

19:50.523 --> 19:54.901
Steven, can't you drive over or
send one of the guys and a car?

19:55.611 --> 19:57.612
Um... Well...

19:59.448 --> 20:00.407
I...

20:01.534 --> 20:03.535
Okay, yeah,
I'll send somebody over.

20:04.120 --> 20:05.078
Great.

20:05.329 --> 20:06.496
What time?

20:06.497 --> 20:09.124
Um... Eight o'clock.

20:11.002 --> 20:12.210
Yeah, okay, I'll try.

20:13.087 --> 20:14.921
Thanks a million, Steven.
Really.

20:17.592 --> 20:18.550
Thank you.

20:24.390 --> 20:26.641
You know, young lady,
there is a telephone,

20:27.143 --> 20:29.102
a pay telephone in the lobby.

20:29.979 --> 20:34.065
Oh, I... I'm terribly sorry,
I didn't realize.

20:34.609 --> 20:36.735
Don't be sorry, you didn't know.

20:37.069 --> 20:39.154
Right. Thanks again.

20:39.739 --> 20:40.697
You're welcome.

20:57.882 --> 21:00.467
[man on tape]
Two rubber baby buggy bumpers.

21:01.552 --> 21:05.388
[Emily] Two rubber
baby buggy bumpers.

21:05.806 --> 21:08.433
[man on tape]
Three Swiss wristwatches.

21:08.434 --> 21:12.145
Three Swiss wristwatches.

21:12.939 --> 21:15.315
[man on tape]
Four thick thistle sticks.

21:15.775 --> 21:19.861
[Emily]
Four thick thistle sticks.

21:21.572 --> 21:25.867
[man on tape] Five buckets of
blue bats and black bug's blood.

21:26.535 --> 21:32.415
[Emily] Five buckets of
